<p>where we caught a train to Calais which we reached about 3.p.m. Then we marched to the sea, went into a rest camp, were issued with tickets for dinner tea &amp; breakfast. Then I had a square meal went to the recreation tent for a little while which is run by the Soldier's Christian Association. Then I went to bed in a tent with 12 in it.</p>
<p>Sunday Jan 13. 1918. 1259<br/>Reveille 5.15 Breakfast</p>
